http://purl.org/dc/elements/1.1/title.value: Washington State K-12 Health and Fitness Standards

http://purl.org/dc/terms/description.value: Washington State has embraced the challenge to ensure that all students become educated and engaged in a lifetime of health and fitness. Teaching our students good health and safety principles can lead to a lifetime of healthy practices, resulting in more productive, active, and successful lives. The essential academic learning requirements (EALRs) in health and fitness establish the concepts and skills necessary for safe and healthy living, and in turn, for successful learning. These guidelines represent the effort to improve the clarity, coherence, inclusiveness, and manageability of our State's standards and the recommended guidelines for health and fitness education.
